i know that babies are supposed to sleep on their backs but is it ok if they put themselves on their side i have a week old and she often rolls on to her side when she sleeps should i leave her or put her on back i am the mother of two wonderful children and a paramedic this is my general rule if they have progressed to the point where they can manipulate themselves into a sleep position then they are big enough to maintain their own airway as they sleep although i tried to keep my son on his back he always rolled onto his belly starting about three months soon after he was up and crawling so long as you keep her crib free of any extra blankets pillows toys and sleep positioners which can be suffocation hazzards if you must use one put it under her mattress she should be just fine don't stress you're a good mom for worrying Mattress Sudden infant death syndrome Professional wrestling holds Bed (furniture) EastEnders Kurt Cobain Suplex Casualty lifting Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Kodocha Childbirth Britney Spears Aerial (dance move) Dog training Professional wrestling throws Knots Landing The Tracey Ullman Show shorts Craps Breech birth Good Vibrations: Thirty Years of The Beach Boys Butterfly stroke The Contender (television series) Humphrey Bogart My Little Pony Shaggy dog story The Dukes of Hazzard R.E.M. (band) Friends Days of our Lives Tag Rugrats Cliff Richard Punishment Breaststroke The Fairly OddParents Who Shot Mr. Burns? Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Paramedic South Park Breastfeeding The Jeffersons (South Park) One Life to Live Lisa's First Word Equine conformation Cribbage Massage Backstroke Social rule Blankets (graphic novel) Whitewater My Life as a Teenage Robot AFI 100 Years series Badminton Co-sleeping Ocean's Twelve Extras (sitcom) Vacuum mattress Care Bears Ja Rule Phil Mitchell 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Sin City Santa Claus Teletubbies The Inside Galactic Civilizations Rock and roll Skateboarding trick Hip hop collaborations 